o'connor read 10 letters from critics on sunday in st. patrick's cathedral at a packed mass celebrating black history month
we may not realize it but deep in our consciousness there is racism,'' the roman catholic archbishop said
the letters ranged from threats to withhold financial support from the church to anger to what one writer referred to as special treatment for black people. o'connor, 68, said he will answer each letter
one writer accused o'connor of ``stirring up racism.'' someone else suggested that the money should go to white people with large families they are trying to put through parochial schools
