the explosion occurred in the resort's maintenance building, a 50-by-75-foot stone and wood structure at the base of the canaan valley ski area. it housed a vehicle maintenance area, an office and six compressors that mixed water and air to make artificial snow
the employees killed were ``snow makers'' and had been performing routine maintenance on one of the six compressors when it exploded. the five other units also were destroyed
